[5] Ecuador (Esmeraldas)
Date: Mon 8 Mar 2009
Source:Fonte: La Hora [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.lahora.com.ec/frontEnd/main.php?idSeccion=845398>


To date in the province, 42 cases of dengue have
been recorded, making Esmeraldas the canton with
the greatest incidence of cases of this tropical
disease. The epidemiologist of the provincial
Health Directorate, Washington Benavides Delgado,
explained that they have 25 confirmed dengue
cases and 18 yet to be verified. Because of this,
control measures have been increased in those
sectors where the cases have been recorded, so that no fatal cases occur.

According to Benavides Delgado, the National
Malaria Eradication Service has materials and
tools to control the proliferation of the
[mosquito] vectors that transmit tropical
diseases. Moreover, they can count on the help of
Esmeraldas Health and the Environment [agencies],
as it relates to promotion and dissemination of
the prevention campaign through communication
media to communities and educational centers when there are classes.

"If there is no citizen participation with help
in cleaning their patios [yards], we can not
eradicate dengue," stated Benavides Delgado.

--
