[7] Brazil (Parana)
Date: Fri 13 Mar 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/pais/cidades/mat/2009/03/13/confirmado-primeiro-caso-de-dengue-hemorragica-no-parana-754818947.asp>


A case of DHF was confirmed by the state
Secretariat of Health in Icaraima, a municipality
in the northwest of Parana [state]. There was
also a reported case of dengue fever with
complications in Cambe, North. Despite the 97
percent decline in the number of cases in Parana
last year, the confirmation of the case was of
concern to the Secretariat of Health because it
shows that the state is not free of the disease this year [2009].

According to the State News Agency, the concern
is because the months in which there is a greater
concentration of cases are precisely March, April
and May. According to the Secretariat, new cases
of DHF could occur this year in view of the large
number of recorded dengue fever [cases] in recent years.

Simple measures can control the disease. The goal
is prevent the mosquito that transmits dengue
[virus] to proliferate, reducing places where still water accumulates.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As noted in the comment above, eliminating
breeding sites of the vector mosquito is, as the
Secretariat indicated, technically simple. Accomplishing it is another thing.

A map of Brazil showing the states can be
accessed at <http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>.
